  "text": "In 2002, Prkcd knockout mice [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] revealed an essential role for this kinase in B-cell homeostasis and tolerance. Due to defective negative selection in germinal centers and autonomous B-cell hyperproliferation in the periphery [CITATION_3] , autoreactive B cells accumulate in these mice. Consequently, Prkcd knockout mice develop systemic autoimmunity evidenced by autoantibodies, immune complex-mediated glomerulonephritis, lymphadenopathy, splenomegaly, and show B-cell infiltration in several organs and tissues [CITATION_4] .",
